BusinessTech has launched a new Android app, which lets you put South Africa’s biggest business news website on your smartphone homescreen. The app is lightweight and responsive, with a clean design and simple interface. Click here to download the BusinessTech Android app “The new BusinessTech Android app works in the same way as the website does on mobile devices,” said Broad Media MD Kevin Lancaster. This means there are no sign-ups or subscriptions required – the app is free to access and use. “Our goal when building the app was clear: make it easy for our readers to access BusinessTech.” “The app is fast and lightweight, and there are no requirements to use it. Just download it and read away.” You can download the BusinessTech Android app from the Google Play store today. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-496109" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-scaled.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="379" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-300x178.jpg 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-1024x607.jpg 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-768x455.jpg 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-1536x910.jpg 1536w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-2048x1214.jpg 2048w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/BusinessTech-App-1200x711.jpg 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" />